The index of refraction of vacuum is 1.  The index of refraction of air
is a little more than 1.  Glass is about 1.4.  Diamond is about 2.4.  The
speed of light in a transparent material medium is slowed relative to the
speed in vacuum in proportion to the refractive index.  Light speed
through a material with a refractive index of 2 is half the speed in a
vacuum.


